  "title": "Core Concepts of Control Structures",
  "lessonText": "Understanding control structures is essential for effective programming in Java.",
  "data": {
    "content": "Control structures in Java allow you to dictate the flow of your program. Here are the key concepts:\n\n- **Conditional Statements**: Use `if`, `else if`, and `else` to execute code based on conditions.\n- **Switch Statements**: A cleaner way to handle multiple conditions based on a single variable.\n- **Loops**: Utilize `for`, `while`, and `do-while` loops to repeat actions.\n- **Break and Continue**: Control the flow within loops with `break` to exit and `continue` to skip iterations.\n\nRefer to the earlier lesson content such as the **Java Full Course for Beginners** and the **Interactive Coding** example to reinforce these concepts. Practice with the **Challenge** to fill in the blanks related to these core concepts."
  }
}
